From: Jani Nikula <jani.nikula@intel.com>
Date: Fri, 22 Aug 2014 15:06:35 +0300
Subject: [PATCH 1153/1369] drm/i915: don't check for i830 in vlv specific
 code
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

commit 6a9e7363775f699388f173bc4fba9c7c5a8626ae upstream.

Signed-off-by: Jani Nikula <jani.nikula@intel.com>
Reviewed-by: Ville Syrjälä <ville.syrjala@linux.intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Daniel Vetter <daniel.vetter@ffwll.ch>
Signed-off-by: Pengyu Ma <pengyu.ma@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/i915/intel_display.c |    2 +-
 1 files changed, 1 insertions(+), 1 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/intel_display.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/intel_display.c
index 266a7e1..1d150b8 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/intel_display.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/intel_display.c
@@ -1533,7 +1533,7 @@ static void vlv_enable_pll(struct intel_crtc *crtc)
 	BUG_ON(!IS_VALLEYVIEW(dev_priv->dev));
 
 	/* PLL is protected by panel, make sure we can write it */
-	if (IS_MOBILE(dev_priv->dev) && !IS_I830(dev_priv->dev))
+	if (IS_MOBILE(dev_priv->dev))
 		assert_panel_unlocked(dev_priv, crtc->pipe);
 
 	I915_WRITE(reg, dpll);
